  "texts": [
    "In this case R 0 (s, s *) ≈ 0.0772 so we are well within the local asymptotic stability regime provided by theorem 2.5(ii).",
    "Thus the solution of the deterministic system should tend toward the disease free equilibrium.",
    "While the stochastic system will not be at equilibrium at this pair (s, s *), we do satisfy the hypothesis of theorem 4.7, and taking C from (4.49), we have C(σ 2 β + σ 2 µ) ≈ 0.0171.",
    "So while the solution of the stochastic system will not be steady, it should stay within these error bars of the deterministic solution.",
    "This is seen to occur in figure 7 where we plot the deterministic solution along with three realizations of the stochastic system for times t ≥ 10."
